@newell can you explain why you are providing this definition of congruence? It seems very unnatural to me (i.e., the choice to represent sets as indexed families, which are not necessarily even injective!).

Why not just use actual `Set`s, and just require that there is a `Set.BijOn` function mapping one to the other which is distance preserving on that set?

As is, you have the strange phenomenon that if you have two different index sets with the same range, then you can't say they are congruent.

